WEBVTT

00:00.802 --> 00:03.046
Welcome to the James River Church Podcast.

00:03.326 --> 00:06.231
You're about to hear another inspirational message.

00:06.251 --> 00:10.197
It's our prayer that this message is an encouragement and blessing to your life.

00:11.059 --> 00:12.821
But not have the opportunity to meet you.

00:12.841 --> 00:14.104
My name is Justin.

00:14.204 --> 00:18.811
I, me and my wife, Elise, have the privilege of pastoring our Joplin campus.

00:18.931 --> 00:21.235
And so we love the opportunity.

00:21.636 --> 00:24.440
We're our 13th year here at James River Church.

00:24.520 --> 00:25.522
Amazing.

00:25.634 --> 00:31.360
But we've got to see God do over the years, and it's a privilege to open God's Word with you tonight.

00:31.420 --> 00:33.562
And I'm grateful for this house.

00:33.662 --> 00:36.785
I'm grateful for our leaders because they believe big.

00:37.786 --> 00:39.067
They lead us to pray big.

00:39.788 --> 00:42.771
Aren't you grateful we see big things because we have a big God?

00:43.752 --> 00:46.615
Which is really what I want to take you to in God's Word tonight.

00:46.635 --> 00:53.521
I want to talk to you tonight about today's posture, tomorrow's possibilities.

00:53.541 --> 00:54.162
Come on.

00:55.330 --> 01:00.416
You know, when I think about the word posture, I initially think about good posture.

01:01.217 --> 01:08.206
We have four kids and our eight-year-old and our six-year-old, we're teaching them right now to have good posture at the dinner table.

01:09.147 --> 01:12.291
We repeat ourselves a lot right now, friends, but we're getting there.

01:13.352 --> 01:16.496
But you know, I did some research about the power of posture.

01:17.156 --> 01:20.220
And I thought I'd share some of that research with you tonight, if you'd like to hear it.

01:20.901 --> 01:25.106
It's quite amazing what I learned that posture has a lot of physical

01:25.250 --> 01:27.492
amazing realities when you have good posture.

01:27.512 --> 01:27.973
Look at this.

01:28.253 --> 01:31.657
The first thing posture does is it reduces lower back pain.

01:32.458 --> 01:32.938
Who knew?

01:33.779 --> 01:38.645
Fewer headaches when you have good posture, increased energy levels.

01:38.725 --> 01:39.265
Let's go.

01:39.285 --> 01:40.286
It's getting better and better.

01:41.207 --> 01:43.610
Less tension in your shoulders and back.

01:43.730 --> 01:44.411
That's a good one.

01:45.132 --> 01:46.613
Increased lung capacity.

01:46.853 --> 01:47.895
Now, I got a pause.

01:47.915 --> 01:48.575
You can't see it.

01:48.775 --> 01:51.779
But this section right here, they're all sitting up in their chairs a little.

01:52.019 --> 01:54.802
I can tell they're already responding to the message.

01:55.362 --> 01:59.527
The section, come on, improve circulation and digestion.

01:59.587 --> 02:00.388
I love this one.

02:02.070 --> 02:04.693
You can appear taller, everybody, if you have good posture.

02:04.733 --> 02:07.757
If you want to appear taller, come on, good posture will get you there.

02:07.777 --> 02:11.361
And then finally, increased self-confidence.

02:11.381 --> 02:14.325
That's a pretty good list for some good posture.

02:15.887 --> 02:22.034
Healthy posture clearly has positive effects on our physical body.

02:22.978 --> 02:31.991
But so too does our spiritual posture, have a massive implications into our spiritual vibrancy as believers.

02:33.233 --> 02:40.383
And how many of you know that physical posture is important, but spiritual posture is essential.

02:41.845 --> 02:48.114
Physical posture may increase self-confidence, but I love this, spiritual posture.

02:48.322 --> 02:50.485
increases God confidence.

02:50.505 --> 03:01.078
And God confidence is the best confidence you and I can walk in every single day because a God confidence says, no weapon formed against me is going to prosper.

03:01.098 --> 03:07.787
A God confidence says, no, greater is he who is in me than he who is in the world.

03:07.867 --> 03:13.234
Oh, a God confidence says, I will see the goodness of the Lord in the land of the living.

03:13.514 --> 03:16.658
A God confidence can see you through any trial.

03:17.282 --> 03:25.231
every difficulty, because when you have a God confidence, there's nothing impossible that you and I cannot experience.

03:26.352 --> 03:33.440
And in 2 Kings, chapter 13, we read a story of a king who has a massive opportunity in front of him.

03:34.762 --> 03:45.394
But it will be a spiritual posture that leads to a lack in his life instead of seeing what God would have done for him and his people.

03:46.242 --> 04:02.789
King Jehoash in the Israelite people are living in the consequences of them turning their hearts from God and turning their hearts towards idols, resulted in the weakening of the nation, the disrepair of the armies, and even the loss of territory.

04:03.871 --> 04:13.106
With the threat of the king of Erem still coming towards them, King Jehoash finally turns to God through the prophet, Elisha.

04:13.666 --> 04:17.871
That's where I want to read together in 2 Kings 13, beginning in verse 14.

04:17.931 --> 04:22.597
It says, Jehoash, king of Israel went down to see him and he wept over him.

04:22.657 --> 04:28.364
My father, my father, he cried, the chariots and horsemen of Israel.

04:29.546 --> 04:32.649
And Elisha said, get a bow in Samaras.

04:32.669 --> 04:33.390
And he did so.

04:34.452 --> 04:37.736
Take the bow in your hands, he said, to the king of Israel.

04:38.176 --> 04:42.802
When he had taken it, Elisha put his hands on the king hands.

04:43.522 --> 04:46.967
Open the east window, he said, and he opened it.

04:47.447 --> 04:52.334
Shoot, Elisha said, and he shot the Lord's arrow of victory.

04:52.354 --> 05:03.109
The arrow of victory over Elisha declared, you will completely destroy the Aromaeans at Aephek.

05:03.129 --> 05:10.098
Now what I want to show you in this passage and in the scriptures that follow, is that we discover three

05:10.242 --> 05:14.746
postures that are necessary in the life of believers.

05:14.847 --> 05:24.716
If we're going to see the supernatural, miraculous power of God that he intends and desires to do in our life and in the generations to come.

05:25.557 --> 05:28.340
In the first posture we see as a posture of faith.

05:29.681 --> 05:36.368
That God will often ask you to take a faith step or action that seems illogical.

05:36.488 --> 05:38.450
Anybody ever had that happen?

05:40.194 --> 05:41.055
Think about this.

05:42.638 --> 05:51.691
Elisha says to King Joach, take your bow and shoot an arrow out the window.

05:51.751 --> 06:00.464
Do you remember they have lost a massive amount of their army?

06:01.426 --> 06:06.834
Their weapons are in short supply, yet the very thing they lack

06:06.914 --> 06:10.338
God, through Elisha, instructs him to shoot.

06:11.139 --> 06:11.299
Why?

06:11.339 --> 06:16.324
Because God doesn't need a huge army to bring a great victory.

06:16.564 --> 06:22.050
He can use the one thing to do what we can never do with all of our strengths.

06:23.091 --> 06:25.454
He says, the thing you lack, I'm asking you to shoot.

06:25.654 --> 06:32.782
But not only did they lack artillery, did you notice he said, shoot it out a window?

06:34.083 --> 06:36.786
And on the other side of that window was not an army.

06:37.986 --> 06:39.968
He's gonna shoot an arrow that would hit no one.

06:41.630 --> 06:43.812
And defeat nothing.

06:45.895 --> 06:51.461
But I want to take you to a very important piece of information the text provides in verse 16.

06:53.063 --> 06:56.867
Take the bow and arrow in your hands, he said, to the king of Israel.

06:56.887 --> 07:02.974
When he had taken it, Elisha put his hands on the king's hands.

07:04.275 --> 07:07.058
Now I wanna show you what's happening here.

07:07.330 --> 07:10.975
Hands are representing the Lord's hands.

07:11.876 --> 07:20.586
And how many know when God's hands are on your hands, it doesn't matter how illogical it seems, on his hands are on your hands.

07:20.807 --> 07:29.978
They're supernatural power attached that can defeat the enemy, that can overcome the situation, and can bring breakthrough when it seems impossible.

07:32.061 --> 07:36.466
Let me encourage you, it's not just your hands praying for that person in the aisles.

07:36.962 --> 07:39.125
God's hands are on your hands.

07:39.445 --> 07:41.949
It's not just your hands going into the workplace.

07:42.269 --> 07:44.372
It's God's hands on your hands.

07:44.612 --> 07:47.196
It's not just your hands building that business.

07:47.216 --> 07:49.359
Oh, God's hands are on your hands.

07:49.459 --> 07:52.904
It's not just your hands in that classroom, in that hospital room.

07:53.805 --> 08:00.514
When God's hands are on your hands, theological requests turn into supernatural victories.

08:02.617 --> 08:06.162
But for all of us, we can think, well, how would that ever happen?

08:08.290 --> 08:08.971
And he didn't know.

08:10.212 --> 08:15.097
How does it make sense to shoot an arrow and yet gain victory?

08:16.278 --> 08:19.201
You know, I remember moving to Springfield in 2011.

08:19.641 --> 08:21.703
I'd moved to go to seminary.

08:21.723 --> 08:24.386
I had long listened to Pastor John's podcast.

08:24.406 --> 08:26.648
So we knew we would be landing at James River.

08:26.688 --> 08:27.769
There was no question.

08:28.390 --> 08:30.171
And I got my classes going.

08:30.192 --> 08:31.213
We started attending.

08:31.593 --> 08:36.818
And I was going to start looking for a part-time job to help supplement income while I was in school.

08:37.282 --> 08:46.673
I don't ever forget in our prayer time, the Lord said, instead of 20 hours of work, I want you to give that 20 hours to the church each week.

08:47.855 --> 08:50.097
I said, well, that doesn't make any logical sense, Lord.

08:51.479 --> 08:53.181
How do you expect me to pay my bills?

08:54.383 --> 08:58.508
He said, you do it, and I'll take care of your bills.

08:59.889 --> 09:03.393
So I took an illogical step through a series of events.

09:03.453 --> 09:07.218
I ended up in the adult ministry's life groups department serving

09:07.490 --> 09:09.012
roughly 20 hours every week.

09:10.334 --> 09:11.035
You know what happens?

09:11.075 --> 09:11.896
I started doing that.

09:13.519 --> 09:16.042
Unexpected scholarships began to come my way.

09:17.224 --> 09:20.789
Scholarships, I remember getting a letter that I did not apply for.

09:20.850 --> 09:24.755
It says, congratulations.

09:24.775 --> 09:28.461
You've been awarded $3,000 in scholarships.

09:29.021 --> 09:32.146
Then there was a time I did an outside organization I applied.

09:32.290 --> 09:37.557
For a $10,000 scholarship, I got the letter, like a week letter, and it was a letter of rejection.

09:38.879 --> 09:41.122
But friends, I listened to Pastor John way too much.

09:41.182 --> 09:43.526
I said, well, that's just, that can change.

09:46.710 --> 09:48.392
And so I prayed and fasted for three weeks.

09:49.033 --> 09:49.834
I'm sorry, three days.

09:50.215 --> 09:52.778
Three weeks would be great, but that's almost three days.

09:55.703 --> 09:58.226
Because Pastor John said, nothing, nothing of fix.

09:58.658 --> 10:00.341
Anything could be fixed with three day fast.

10:00.381 --> 10:01.883
And so again, I just had it in my mind.

10:01.903 --> 10:03.947
I said, I'm going to pray and God's going to change this.

10:04.107 --> 10:08.314
And you know, it was three weeks later, I got an email and with no explanation.

10:08.695 --> 10:12.080
It says we've decided to award you the $10,000 scholarship.

10:12.100 --> 10:12.321
Why?

10:12.361 --> 10:17.610
Because illogical steps of faith lead to supernatural victories.

10:18.591 --> 10:20.274
Some here tonight you're walking

10:20.354 --> 10:21.736
You've taken a step of faith.

10:21.776 --> 10:23.559
Can I just tell you, God has with you.

10:23.839 --> 10:24.700
He's for you.

10:24.981 --> 10:29.467
He's fighting and victories on the other side of a posture of faith.

10:29.548 --> 10:29.868
Amen.

10:30.309 --> 10:33.233
One number two is a posture of obedience.

10:33.253 --> 10:40.584
Obedience is the prerequisite for greater opportunities and victories in God's kingdom.

10:41.545 --> 10:42.887
Wouldn't you notice verse 18?

10:44.129 --> 10:46.613
Then he said, take the arrows.

10:48.055 --> 10:50.258
In the first instruction, he was

10:50.658 --> 10:53.021
asked to take an arrow, a single arrow.

10:54.022 --> 10:56.485
He obeyed and now watched.

10:56.686 --> 10:57.767
Opportunities growing.

10:57.847 --> 10:59.109
Now take the arrows.

10:59.229 --> 11:00.370
He's going to see something bigger.

11:01.251 --> 11:02.092
And the king took them.

11:02.953 --> 11:04.876
And Elisha told him, strike the ground.

11:04.916 --> 11:08.080
He struck it three times and stopped.

11:09.141 --> 11:16.210
The man of God was angry with him and said, you should have struck the ground five or six times.

11:17.730 --> 11:21.996
The king takes three arrows and begins shooting him into the ground and he stops.

11:23.098 --> 11:24.060
Questions why?

11:24.080 --> 11:26.864
Did Elisha tell him to stop?

11:27.625 --> 11:27.885
No.

11:28.646 --> 11:29.848
Did he run out of arrows?

11:29.928 --> 11:35.897
Apparently not, because Elisha said you should have shot five or six, which means he had five or six arrows to shoot.

11:37.319 --> 11:41.726
But if he had five or six arrows and he only shot three, what is scripture trying to tell us?

11:42.808 --> 11:45.031
He did half of what he could have done.

11:45.852 --> 11:46.994
It's a half-hearted king.

11:47.714 --> 11:48.916
He kind of obeyed.

11:49.497 --> 11:56.190
But how many know partial obedience in the kingdom of God is actually disobedience?

11:56.210 --> 11:57.352
He got tired of shooting.

11:57.372 --> 11:59.035
He thought, this ought to be good enough.

11:59.856 --> 12:01.399
I know I should, but you know what?

12:01.539 --> 12:03.263
I don't feel like shooting six arrows.

12:03.403 --> 12:05.106
I'm going to shoot three.

12:05.858 --> 12:08.181
partial obedience is disobedience in the Kingdom of God.

12:08.201 --> 12:23.578
What an amazing sermon we heard on Sunday from Pastor John on living in obedience to the Word of God because it's obedience to the Word of God that introduces the power of God that transforms our life and open the door for the supernatural to take place.

12:26.101 --> 12:32.449
But it's disobedience that results in something much less than God would have intended.

12:32.509 --> 12:33.650
Look at verse 19.

12:35.106 --> 12:39.653
The man of God was angry with him and said, you should have struck the ground five or six times.

12:40.074 --> 12:44.842
Then you would have defeated Aram and completely destroyed it.

12:46.024 --> 12:51.292
But now you will defeat it only three times.

12:52.574 --> 12:55.058
Disobedience, friends, is very costly.

12:55.778 --> 12:57.480
And it never just affects you.

12:57.720 --> 12:59.743
This is going to affect the nation.

12:59.763 --> 13:12.879
And not only that, it's going to affect the generations that come after him as they are defeated by their enemy because of the lack of obedience in the king's life to honor the word of the Lord.

13:14.240 --> 13:15.923
But the other side is true too.

13:17.044 --> 13:25.394
Wholehearted obedience leads to more in God's kingdom because wholehearted obedience leads to a supernatural power in your life.

13:25.922 --> 13:28.947
and your future that multiplies your miracles.

13:28.967 --> 13:29.488
Did you notice?

13:29.768 --> 13:34.536
You would have defeated all of them completely defeated.

13:35.517 --> 13:50.121
If you would have just done what the word of the Lord said, and I can encourage you tonight, God wants to pour His blessing on your life, on your family, on your future legacy, but tomorrow's blessings begin with today's obedience.

13:51.383 --> 13:52.604
Well, there's a third posture.

13:52.625 --> 13:53.586
It's the posture of heart.

13:54.498 --> 14:00.026
Our response to God's instruction reveals the condition of our heart.

14:01.528 --> 14:07.376
I believe if we were to do a spiritual autopsy on King Jehoshaphat's heart, we'd find a few things.

14:08.278 --> 14:14.466
I think we'd find first that he had a heart that wanted God's power but wasn't interested in God's plan.

14:16.069 --> 14:20.295
You see, when you begin to dissect this scenario, the king was desperate for God's power.

14:20.675 --> 14:22.738
He wanted to be rescued no doubt.

14:24.002 --> 14:35.506
But his lack of obedience demonstrated that he was more interested in God's hand of power than God's heart.

14:35.970 --> 14:38.732
just God's hand to get us out of a situation.

14:39.033 --> 14:42.195
We miss what God has so much more intended for us.

14:42.536 --> 14:44.037
He wants us to know his heart.

14:44.397 --> 14:52.524
He wants us to know his ways because it's not gonna be the last battle you face, but how many know when God brings you through a battle, when you know his heart?

14:52.745 --> 15:01.252
Like we heard last Wednesday night, he is good and he does good, that when you go into that next battle, you stand and you say, no, I watched God deliver me last time.

15:01.492 --> 15:04.094
He's a good God and he is with me today.

15:04.355 --> 15:05.956
And I know his ways.

15:05.936 --> 15:09.280
His ways are powerful and His ways are miraculous.

15:09.540 --> 15:11.803
And I will see Him bring me through.

15:14.566 --> 15:19.472
Secondly, we see a heart that was more concerned with image than integrity.

15:21.554 --> 15:28.602
No doubt is a powerful king and he's shooting arrows into the ground.

15:28.622 --> 15:30.044
Probably thinking, what am I doing?

15:31.345 --> 15:32.146
I'm a king.

15:33.442 --> 15:36.487
I should be shooting these arrows at the enemy, not in the ground.

15:38.129 --> 15:39.912
At some point he got his eyes off of God.

15:40.933 --> 15:41.975
He got it on to himself.

15:42.896 --> 15:43.678
And what he looked like.

15:43.738 --> 15:45.200
I look like a fool doing this.

15:45.781 --> 15:46.442
What are we doing here?

15:46.462 --> 15:48.605
We're already short artillery.

15:51.450 --> 15:55.195
But God wanted to do so much more in his life.

15:56.658 --> 15:59.121
But he got his eyes off the real thing.

16:00.363 --> 16:02.226
And when we're more concerned with our image,

16:02.882 --> 16:11.933
than our integrity, we forfeit the victories that God wanted to bring into our lives, because it's all about him and his glory.

16:13.114 --> 16:18.901
Finally, it reveals a heart that lacked enthusiasm and whole-hearted commitment.

16:20.883 --> 16:25.749
King Jehoah stopped striking because his heart was in a dark place.

16:27.612 --> 16:29.714
His heart was not full on for the Lord,

16:30.530 --> 16:40.401
So instead of enthusiastically responding to God's instruction, he instead responded with how he felt instead of what God said.

16:42.804 --> 16:58.322
What this story shows as friends is both the devastating results of a half-hearted faith, but it also gives us insight into what God's heart is for those who position their lives

16:58.402 --> 17:02.327
with a wholehearted love and commitment to the Lord.

17:03.889 --> 17:12.018
Greater victories are on the other side of a whole heart of an obedient heart of a heart that will step out in faith.

17:12.038 --> 17:16.404
The good news for you and me is that we don't have to respond like King Jehoash did.

17:16.444 --> 17:18.947
We can respond with a posture of faith.

17:20.409 --> 17:26.136
It says God, it doesn't matter how illogical what you're asking me to do things.

17:27.477 --> 17:28.178
If you say it,

17:29.154 --> 17:31.176
I'll step out.

17:31.196 --> 17:31.637
I'll do it.

17:33.099 --> 17:41.288
For some, that step, that illogical step of faith is to begin giving the first to the Lord in your finances.

17:41.328 --> 17:45.273
You know, tithing is a new logical step.

17:45.293 --> 17:50.999
It makes no sense how we can give the first to God and he'll do more with 90 than we could ever do with 100.

17:51.059 --> 17:53.522
It doesn't make sense unless God's hand is on your hand.

17:55.682 --> 17:57.208
Some, it's a posture of obedience.

17:57.309 --> 17:59.056
God, I'll do whatever you say to do.

17:59.257 --> 18:02.210
You know, there's some, that posture of obedience is getting baptized.

18:02.230 --> 18:02.973
You've been saved.

18:03.033 --> 18:04.399
It's time to get baptized.

18:04.439 --> 18:06.066
That's first step of obedience.

18:06.530 --> 18:10.354
For some in this New Year, it's to get in a freedom group, it's to say, you know what?

18:10.374 --> 18:14.959
I'm not gonna allow this to continue to dominate my life.

18:14.980 --> 18:16.782
This is a year I'm gonna get free.

18:17.042 --> 18:21.827
I'm gonna walk in obedience to the Lord, and I'm gonna see Him do something powerful in my life.

18:21.847 --> 18:23.189
I'm gonna get in a life group.

18:23.229 --> 18:29.095
I'm gonna get on a dream team, and I'm gonna watch how God uses community to propel my future forward.

18:30.677 --> 18:34.962
Have a heart that says, God, I'm just whole, hearted free.

18:36.994 --> 18:39.619
God wants to strengthen every single person in this room at night.

18:40.842 --> 18:46.494
And I love how God responds to a person whose whole heart did look at 2 Chronicles 6-19.

18:47.736 --> 18:53.227
The eyes of the Lord search the whole earth in order to strengthen those whose hearts are what?

18:54.069 --> 18:56.755
Fully committed to Him.

18:56.775 --> 18:58.418
He wants to strengthen you tonight.

